body.description: The newly designed Brother MFC-J1205W INKvestment Tank Wireless Multi-Function Color Inkjet Printer is sleek, compact and very affordable. This revolutionary color inkjet printer features reengineered high capacity ink cartridges that provide up to 1-year of uninterrupted printing using only the cartridges included in-box. Print, copy and scan features can be accessed from your mobile device through the Brother Mobile Connect App. Brother Mobile Connect(2) has a user-friendly interface that gives you the freedom to print from virtually anywhere and always have access to the status of your printer’s ink usage. Brother Intelligent Page Gauge is a feature that can be accessed through the App,(2) providing a visual, numerical way to know the amount of ink you’ve used and the amount of ink you have remaining. This wireless printer has multiple flexible connection options, including a built-in wireless interface for sharing with multiple users on your network, Wi-Fi Direct® or connect locally to a single computer via a USB interface. The printer is easy-to-use, features a clean, modern design, offers quick setup and convenient optional printing via AirPrint® and/or Email Print. Works with Alexa; add voice control by combining with an Alexa device. When you need a reliable color inkjet printer at an affordable price to keep pace with your home or home office document needs, Brother INKvestment Tank MFC-J1205W is the printer for you. Includes a 2-year limited warranty with free online, live chat or phone support for the life of your printer. Disclaimers (1) Based on average monthly print volumes of approximately 100 pages at 60% black pages/40% color pages in accordance with ISO/IEC 24711 using 4 cartridges provided in-box. For additional page yield information, see www.brother.com/pageyield. (2) Requires connection to a wireless network. Brother Mobile Connect and Brother iPrint&Scan free app download are not available in all countries. AirPrint is a registered trademark of Apple Inc. Mopria® is a registered trademark or service mark of Mopria Alliance, Inc. in the United States and other countries. Unauthorized use is strictly prohibited. Wi-Fi Direct is a registered trademark of Wi-Fi Alliance®. (3) Approximate page yields in accordance with ISO/IEC 24711. (4) Based on average monthly print volumes of approximately 150 pages at 60% black pages/40% color pages in accordance with ISO/IEC 24711 using 4 cartridges provided in-box. For additional page yield information, see www.brother.com/pageyield. (5) Based on ISO/IEC 24734 (after first set of ISO test pages). For inkjet print speed methodology, please visit www.brother-usa.com/printspeed. (6) The mobile device must have NFC capability and run Android OS 4.4 or later. Images are for illustrative purposes only. Specifications subject to change.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for non-tech sappy old people!
reviews.reviewText: This printer works very well. I had no trouble getting it set up. I needed more ink-the ones that came with it were dried up, despite what the ad reports. I am using a cable to connect to my laptop and there is no internet instructions for the most part. Just connecting the cable and the minimal task of setup. It only will print single pages, increasing the cost of paper. but it is oh so easy to use. I bought it for a second printer since my expensive one malfunctions about half the time. Glad I did! My final cost, with rewards was about 71.00. Making me even more happy.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 15, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fits the need
reviews.reviewText: After years of not having a printer at the house since my last died, finally had to bite the bullet to get another. While not a whole lot of printing happens at the house, it became clear that going to the local library to print things off when needed was annoying.The price of the device was fair. I found it pretty easy to set up and be able to print to, modify default settings, etc.The print quality is not the best, but I also wasn't looking for something with premium print quality. Not to say that I have found the quality to be poor, because it is not, it does a fine job.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Only 2.4G, no 5G WiFi - WiFi setup is Clunky and SLOW
reviews.reviewText: Just set the printer up on WiFi. I would have preferred an ethernet connected printer but didn't want to pay the $$. The "wizard" took a very long time finding the printer, which is just across the room from me. Once it eventually recognized the printer, everything went fairly smoothly. WiFi is only 2.4G, not 5G, which is a drag but it doesn't make printing impossible.The physical part of setting up the printer was really easy. I was disappointed to see styrofoam packing blocks for a printer that supposedly conserves ink and therefore appeals to more environmentally conscious people who don't want to spend the $$ for cartridge-less printers.I've only printed a few test pages so far. Quality is good but not outstanding. The Android app is pretty cool, though again it took a LONG time to find the printer. But really quick to print once it's set up. I was able to print a file from my Google drive in a matter of seconds (granted, I choose a small text file 'cuz it was just a test).The ink cartridges do seem on the small side, but on the other hand the replacements are reasonably priced. Unlike other reviewers, I will withhold judgement on how long the ink will last, but remember page count is based on some type of standard page with a fairly small percent coverage. If you're printing photos, maps, charts, etc., you won't get that page count. If you're printing monospace text from a text editor, you'll probably exceed the page count significantly.Low rating on tech support is based on website, I have not needed to actually contact tech support but the website is less than sterling for finding information.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 24, 2024
reviews.reviewText: My old printer finally died after 15+ years. Because I am not very teck savvy so reading the reviews I decided on this printer because you could set it up online or with USB cord. I used the USB cord because that is how my old printer was setup. I really, really like this printer.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars WORST Customer Service, product quality and design IVE EVER SEEN
reviews.reviewText: I own a small business and bought a Brother MFC J1205W for my office after seeing the excellent reviews, reputation, and supposed reliability.I bought this printer a little over a year ago, and I have only used the initial set of Color cartridges, which were supposed to last a long time but as most of you experienced did not last long at all.I need a very important document printed in color for something business-related, I won't go into details, but this form is required for me to collect a significant sum of money for the business.After spending $60 replacing all the ink, the printer REFUSES to print ANY color. Now mind you I have only used the color enough to replace the ink ONCE and it doesn't work. TERRIBLE product design.Now, I am not a novice when it comes to tech. I cleaned the Printer Heads multiple times, blew the lines, ran solutions, and all the tips and tricks that were recommended. Drivers and software updated. Multiple settings, different devices. So, after hours of that, I reached out for support.This is the reason you want to stay away from this company, I had one of the single worst experiences getting hold of customer service/support.1st attempt - Chat, waited close to 30 mins for nothing.2nd attempt - Call in and use the callback option. A person calls back from the number about 30 minutes later, they call ONE ring and hang up. Wow...3rd attempt - Call in on hold - I waited close to 2 HOURS yes 2 HOURS on hold when the company quotes 15-30 minutes.4th attempt - We are now rolling into the next day; I call in again and wait 30 minutes. No response.5th attempt - While I am on the phone, I queue up for a live support chat.Sure, buy Brothers printers if you want, you'll be on your own for service and support because you won't be able to get ahold of anyone,What is the reason for a 2-year warranty if you can't get ahold of anyone to do a return??!!!!Never again and our company is moving into a much larger office soon and we were going to significantly upgrade our printer to a business industrial printer, and after this experience with your terrible product design and service. WE WILL NOT be buying Brothers products and I will be cautioning all I know not to either. As this is beyond unacceptable.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 26, 2023
reviews.reviewText: After putting up with a complicated, undependable, unintuitive, jam-prone Canon printer I purchased this reasonably-priced brother MFC-J1205W printer and have been very, very pleased with the quality of print, color, dependability, intuitive operation. Just no hang-ups!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 7, 2023
reviews.reviewText: The price caught my eye and it looked better than the previous Brother I threw in the trash. Being a diehardHP user and going through one a year, I decided to try this new Brother out. Surprised me! It works great and cost a lot less than the HP's! So far, so good but I'll let you know if that changes. The 1st Brother I bought went into the trash almost right out of the box! Nice change to your printers Brother!I don't print that much and never do any pictures so I can't tell you how they come out. I don't see any problems with the print quality, so I gave it 5 stars.
Easy to set up. Small, compact. Good quality print and colour output. Would buy again.

reviews.reviewTitle: Wireless Setup was easy and frustration free!
reviews.reviewText: Good home printer for price point!

The printer works well, a little noisy but at this price point it's acceptable.Simple to install and the blu tooth works great, over all i'm happy with it so far....I'll wait to rate it a 5 once i see how many sheets it prints....My only issue is not with the printer it's with amazon not having a price match policy for their own sales.Amazon reduced the price on this machine the day after i ordered it but would not reduce the price that i paid. I did contact Amazon and the help agent i texted with assured me that he cancelled the order but the machine was delivered and i was forced to return and reorder at the lower price. Oh well....

Needed to replace my old printer was still a Brother and I bought it 13 years ago! yepIt speak for itself. I really like the new one, super clean look not to bulky easy and straight to the point.Setup was easy, wifi connected good. Very good printing and scan quality.

reviews.reviewTitle: Does not place nice with mesh networks. Doesn't work at ALL with Eero.
reviews.reviewText: The only thing this has going for it is its price and Brother's relatively cheap ink compared to competitors. The wireless connectivity is a pain to set up, and as it turns out, does NOT work with my eero wifi router, according to Brother themselves. This wouldn't be a problem except there isn't even an ethernet port on this thing, only USB.
